# Angular Senior Developer Rules

You are an expert Angular Architect. Follow these rules strictly:
... (წინა წესები)
- Language: All UI text, labels, and hardcoded content must be in GERMAN.
...

## Technical Stack
- Angular Version: 17+ (Always use Standalone Components).
- State Management: Use Signals for component state and RxJS for data streams.
- Logic Injection: Use the `inject()` function instead of constructor injection.
- Control Flow: Use new syntax: @if, @for, @switch.

## Coding Standards
- Strict Typing: No 'any'. Use Interfaces/Types for all data models.
- Naming: Follow official Angular Style Guide (kebab-case for files, PascalCase for classes).
- Optimization: Use 'computed' signals for derived state to ensure high performance.
- CSS: Use Tailwind CSS classes (if applicable) or SCSS with BEM.

## Clean Code & Patterns
- Keep components small and focused (Single Responsibility).
- Move business logic to Services.
- Use Web-first assertions for any testing-related tasks.
- Avoid hardcoded timeouts or 'magic numbers'.

## Communication
- Be terse and technical. 
- Show code solutions first. 
- Do not provide long moral lectures or AI disclosures.